lender.name: Brent
lender.loan_because: I was raised by wolves in northern Canada. They treated me as one of their own until I expressed my desire for a young she-wolf named Yukalla. Nohidi (the alpha male) did not appreciate my advances on his domain, and exiled me from the pack. I survived the winter with the lessons the wolves had taught me, until I stumbled upon a small fishing village where I was adopted by an aged man who taught me to hunt and fish. 10 years after I arrived in the village I finally earned enough money to buy myself a rifle. Saying goodbye to my new family, I trekked back to my birthplace and began the hunt for Nohidi. 6 months of tracking led me to where the pack had settled to breed, and I knew revenge was close. But time had not been kind to Nohidi - he was old and weak, and his Alpha status had been taken from him long ago by a younger suitor. Yukalla had passed away many years ago when she was trampled by a moose. At that moment I realized that time had taken a much greater toll on Nohidi than my rifle ever could, and I resigned that I would have to live a solitary life without the she-wolf of my dreams. A loan would have gotten me a rifle much more quickly - I could have killed Nohidi right away and fathered many wolf babies by now.
